     =========================================================
 		  Geant4 - Microdosimetry example
     =========================================================

                                README file
                          ----------------------

                           CORRESPONDING AUTHOR 

S. Incerti
Centre d'Etudes Nucleaires de Bordeaux-Gradignan 
(CENBG), IN2P3 / CNRS / Bordeaux 1 University, 33175 Gradignan, France
e-mail:incerti@cenbg.in2p3.fr

This advanced example shows the use of Geant4 DNA physics processes in a 
liquid water high resolution 3D cellular phantom, irradiated with one alpha+ 
(Helium ionized once, as delivered by the CENBG irradiation facility) particle 
of 1.5 keV.

The code architecture and use are taken from the microbeam advanced example. 
Please refer to this advanced example more more details.

The $G4LEDATA directory must contain the 'dna' directory with all set of data
files.
